  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study intend to evaluate the effectiveness of functional orthoses
      (including custom-made insoles and shoes) for preventing and controlling repetitive
      haemarthrosis in patients suffering of haemophilic ankle arthropathy, as well as the
      orthoses' impact on foot health-related quality of life.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
